Michelle Carter convicted of sending text messages inciting Conrad Roy's suicide
A Massachusetts woman was sentenced to two years in prison for inciting her boyfriend to commit suicide through text messages and phone calls.
Twenty-year-old Michelle Carter is serving 15 months of a two-year prison sentence before serving five years on probation.
Carter was convicted in June for the unintentional killing of Conrad Roy, who took his own life on July 13, 2014.
